text: Walker County is a county of the U.S. state of Alabama. "ACES Winston County Office" (links/history), Alabama Cooperative Extension System (ACES), 2007, webpage: ACES-Walker. Its name is in honor of John Williams Walker, a member of the United States Senate. As of the 2020 census, the population was 65,342. Its county seat is Jasper. ==References== Category:Alabama counties Category:1820s establishments in Alabama Category:1823 establishments in the United States
